Text:
Guess she managed to 
 fit all that furniture 
 inside, even if the 
 house couldn't take it.
Well, could you cut down \n on your luggage then?
It's empty. \n Did she move again?

I heard the floor caved 
 in, wonder how much 
 weight the old owner 
 had sitting on it?

Hm? What happened to 
 the house? Didn't it 
 belong to that woman 
 from Havina?
Load the Belongings \n on to the Airboat
Formerly Rich Woman: \n Start with this one.
Hey! Would you mind \n helping me with a little \n moving job?
It's not going to \n involve anything \n smelly, is it?
No, no, nothing like \n that this time.
Though it might take \n a little skill to \n pull the job off.
This is the woman \n who needs help moving.
She's that rich women \n who was throwing the \n parties in Havina.
She's moving to Lei \n Colmosna.
And she needs someone \n to help her get all her \n stuff to the new place.
A rich woman \n moving from Havina \n to Colmosna?
Maybe it's best I \n don't ask the details.
Alright, I think I can \n handle this!
Okay then, just get all \n this stuff on to the \n moving boat for me.
Formerly Rich Woman: \n And that one.
Formerly Rich Woman: \n Oh, and that one.
Formerly Rich Woman: \n And those ones.
Formerly Rich Woman: \n Those ones too.
Formerly Rich Woman: \n Oh, I almost forgot that one.
Formerly Rich Woman: \n I couldn't bear leaving that behind.
Formerly Rich Woman: \n Now just get all of this on the moving boat.

What!? How am I 
 supposed to fit all 
 that on this little 
 boat?
It's the best I could \n do, all of the other \n boats are out on jobs.
Guess you'll just have \n to make multiple trips.
And swallow those fuel \n costs? I think not.
Things are tight lately, \n I can't afford that.

The woman who was 
 burning fuel for parties 
 is worried about 
 conserving it now?

Absolutely not. Those 
 pieces have all been in 
 the family for 
 generations.
For someone moving on \n down, she's still as \n demanding as ever...
Just stack it up, we'll \n figure out the rest.
Won't it fall? Are you \n going to be able to \n steer the boat?
Don't worry! I've \n driven under worse \n conditions.
Great... So much \n for that way out.

Let's get going, 
 partner. I've got 
 another job. We've 
 got 3 minutes.
3 minutes!? \n I better hurry.
It's all packed, \n what a relief.
Nice going! I'll take \n care of the rest.
I hope nothing breaks...
Lady, your stuff is all \n waiting for you at the \n new place.
Thank you very much.

And thank you, miss. 
 Here's a little 
 something for your 
 trouble.

Really? I thought you 
 couldn't bear to part 
 with any of your 
 furniture?

The new place is too 
 crowded anyway. 
 I needed to let go 
 of a few things.
Wish she would've \n come to that realization \n before moving...
*Beep* *Beep*
Hm?
We're flooded over here!
Your new pile-it-high \n service is a big hit.
Wow, word travels fast!
Looks like I'm gonna be \n busier than ever!
The moving boat piled to the sky soon became \n a famous sight in Jirga Para Lhao.
I need to hurry if I want to get all of this on.
Doing good so far.
Uh-oh, I better pick up the pace.
Not bad, not bad.
Why does she have to have so much stuff!?
Job's all done!
I need to hurry!

Shoot, I'm out of time!
I need to move faster...
Moving Job

I need to be more careful...
